        public java.util.ArrayList<int[]> readUpdateRecord()
        reads the update table, and returns an integer representation of the results. This seemed the most lightweight way to accomplish this.
        Returns:
        - integer array [0] = id# of the row changed [1] = table that was changed (see insertUpdateRecord) [2] = type of change (see insertUpdateRecord)
